  "text": "The research shows that satisfaction may be influenced by emotions (albeit with a combination of other factors), as well as personal disposition (optimist or pessimist) (cf. [CITATION_1] . Optimism can be defined as 'one's general expectation of successful and favourable outcomes' [CITATION_2] . Level of optimism can be included among personality traits, and research has shown a connection between optimism and life satisfaction [CITATION_3] . Personality 4 variables were used to measure the level of optimism.",
